@startuml
title ShopSmart - Deployment Diagram (Horizontal Scaling)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle

node "Client Device" {
    component "Web Browser / Mobile App" as Client
}

cloud "Vercel (Main Server)" {
    node "Vercel Edge Network (Auto-scaling)" {
        component "Next.js Serverless Instance 1" as Vercel1
        component "Next.js Serverless Instance N" as VercelN
    }
}

cloud "Render (Backend API)" {
    component "Render Load Balancer" as RenderLB
    
    node "Express.js Auto-scaling Cluster" {
        component "API Node 1" as API1
        component "API Node 2" as API2
        component "API Node N" as APIN
    }
}

cloud "AWS (Infrastructure)" {
    node "Amazon S3 & CloudFront" {
        artifact "Static Assets & Media" as CDN
    }
    
    database "Amazon RDS Multi-AZ (PostgreSQL)" {
        component "Primary Database" as DB_Primary
        component "Read Replica" as DB_Replica
    }
}

Client <--> CDN : Fetch Static Assets (HTTPS)
Client <--> Vercel1 : HTTPS Request
Client <--> VercelN : HTTPS Request

Vercel1 <--> RenderLB : Proxy API Calls (HTTPS)
VercelN <--> RenderLB : Proxy API Calls (HTTPS)

RenderLB ==> API1 : Route Traffic
RenderLB ==> API2 : Route Traffic
RenderLB ==> APIN : Route Traffic

API1 <--> DB_Primary : Read/Write (TCP/IP)
API2 <--> DB_Primary : Read/Write (TCP/IP)
APIN <--> DB_Primary : Read/Write (TCP/IP)

API1 --> CDN : Upload Media
API2 --> CDN : Upload Media

DB_Primary ..> DB_Replica : Async Replication

note Bottom of Vercel1
  Vercel is the main server handling
  frontend SSR and auto-scaling.
end note

note Right of APIN
  Render provides horizontal scaling
  and load balancing for the Node.js API.
end note

note Bottom of DB_Replica
  AWS handles highly available database
  replication and scalable object storage.
end note

@enduml
